{"name":"Incredible Golem Companion","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You’ve expanded your golem companion's magical structure. It becomes an incredible construct companion.</p>\n<p>When your golem companion succeeds at a saving throw against a magic effect that deals their warded energy damage, they get a critical success, instead.</p>\n<p>When your golem companion fails at a saving throw against a magic effect that deals their vulnerable energy damage, they get a critical failure, instead.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"incredible-golem-companion","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":10},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Advanced Golem Companion"},{"value":"expert in your spellcasting tradition"},{"value":"master in Crafting"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686123512179,"modifiedTime":1686335003723,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"3jaKSLp4cjDhyIQz"}
{"name":"Golem Antimagic","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You push your golem’s defenses against their warded energy. For you, @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.magic-specializations-spells.8Y6RIXIAaWWil9SI]{Heal Golem} is a cantrip and doesn’t require a Focus Point to cast. At 20th level, you can cast @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.magic-specializations-spells.8Y6RIXIAaWWil9SI]{Heal Golem} as a free action with the same trigger.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"golem-antimagic","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":18},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Golem Healing"},{"value":"Paragon Golem Companion"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686123512179,"modifiedTime":1686334989474,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"613FQuWd6Bw2aK4u"}
{"name":"Golem’s Strike","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You have imbued your golem companion with your cantrips. You gain the @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.magic-specializations-spells.OE1NCLeV0uBflpOP]{Golem Strike} focus spell, and increase your focus pool by 1 Focus Point.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[{"key":"ActiveEffectLike","mode":"add","path":"system.resources.focus.max","value":1}],"slug":"golems-strike","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":8},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Advanced Golem Companion"},{"value":"you have a cantrip with the attack trait"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686123512179,"modifiedTime":1686335010471,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"8bxogt5vkg4a8pK3"}
{"name":"Golem Prototyper Dedication","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><strong>Access </strong>You have been instructed in golemcrafting or found a prototype golem.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You have invested a portion of your spellcasting power into a prototype golem, providing positive energy that animates it with a rudimentary approximation of a soul.</p>\n<p>You gain a prototype construct companion known as your golem companion, with the following modifications: Your construct companion has the magical and golem traits, and they have only one kind of melee unarmed attack, which deals 1d8 bludgeoning, piercing, or slashing damage (chosen when you first gain the companion) and has the magical trait.</p>\n<p>Depending on the shape of your construct this could be a fist, retractable blade, jaws, or other similar unarmed attack.</p>\n<p>Your golem companion gains  a +1 status bonus to AC and saving throws against spells. Choose a type of material (stone, glass, bone, clay, etc.) that your golem companion is primarily made of.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Special </strong>You can’t select another dedication feat until you’ve gained two other feats from the @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-magic-journals.6DPJqrJJBdYR5hbz.JournalEntryPage.71UUG2KsCC66tKuH]{Golem Prototyper} archetype. </p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"golem-prototyper-dedication","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":2},"traits":{"value":["archetype","dedication"],"rarity":"uncommon"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"trained in a spellcasting tradition"},{"value":"trained in Crafting"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686123512179,"modifiedTime":1686334968541,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"HmW1VFOj20qAaZBY"}
{"name":"Golem’s March","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You can direct your golem companion to make an inexorable march. You gain the @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.magic-specializations-spells.hDVVGEVs1KjbCdRg]{Golem’s March} focus spell and increase your focus pool by 1 Focus Point.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[{"key":"ActiveEffectLike","mode":"add","path":"system.resources.focus.max","value":1}],"slug":"golems-march","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":4},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Golem Prototyper Dedication"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.SZs3vRWh5MtIQe4B"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686123512179,"modifiedTime":1686335060540,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"Ket6Dtc39krguUf2"}
{"name":"Golem Healing","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You ward your golem companion to invert damage into healing. You gain the @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.magic-specializations-spells.8Y6RIXIAaWWil9SI]{Heal Golem} focus spell, and increase your focus pool by 1 Focus Point.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[{"key":"ActiveEffectLike","mode":"add","path":"system.resources.focus.max","value":1}],"slug":"golem-healing","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":8},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Advanced Golem Companion"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686123512179,"modifiedTime":1686335029420,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"LIlFxJj5D4xqEkhu"}
{"name":"Paragon Golem Companion","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You've refined your golem companion to its peak performance. It becomes a paragon construct companion.</p>\n<p>Your golem companion becomes immune to its warded energy damage.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"paragon-golem-companion","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":16},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Incredible Golem Companion"},{"value":"master in your spellcasting tradition"},{"value":"legendary in Crafting"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686123512179,"modifiedTime":1686334997054,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"OdPtMYApoeVpueS8"}
{"name":"Golem Speaker","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>Your connection with your golem allows you to communicate with constructs. Even if a construct is mindless or can’t normally speak, as long as your golem companion is nearby, you can connect with a construct’s latent willpower and programming to ask questions of them and receive answers. A construct’s perspective, perception, and knowledge give it a worldview different enough from a human’s that it doesn't consider the same details important. They can mostly answer questions about creatures that created or have interacted with them in the past and what their general instructions are.</p>\n<p>You can use Crafting instead of Diplomacy to make simple requests of constructs.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"golem-speaker","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":4},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Golem Prototyper Dedication"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686123512179,"modifiedTime":1686335056191,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"fhOoAu3oCX3aeeIh"}
{"name":"Advanced Golem Companion","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You've upgraded your golem companion's magical power and decision-making ability. It becomes an advanced construct companion. During an encounter, even if you don't use the Command a Minion action, your golem companion can still use 1 action on your turn that round to Stride or Strike.</p>\n<p>Choose acid, cold, electricity, fire, or sonic as your golem companion’s warded energy. Your golem companion gains resistance to this type of energy damage equal to your level.</p>\n<p>Your GM then chooses one of the remaining types of energy damage as your golem companion’s vulnerable energy. Your golem companion gains weakness to this type of energy damage equal to half your level rounded up.</p>\n<p>Then, choose one of the remaining types of energy damage as your golem companion’s slowing energy. When your golem companion takes this type of energy damage, they don’t gain their 1 action if you don’t Command them on your next turn.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"advanced-golem-companion","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":6},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Golem Prototyper Dedication"},{"value":"expert in Crafting"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686123512179,"modifiedTime":1686335048824,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"g8AkOKH9t9psFxPU"}
{"name":"Golem Decoder","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You speak persuasively to a construct to learn its passcode. Attempt a Crafting check against a construct’s Will DC. On a success, you learn the passcode that will deactivate it (or learn that there is no such passcode).</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"golem-decoder","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":7},"traits":{"value":["archetype","skill"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Golem Speaker"},{"value":"master in Crafting"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686123512179,"modifiedTime":1686335033905,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"v6r04S3rJ8By8yIK"}
